  "prompt_type": "cognitive",
  "prompt_text": "What are the ACID properties of database transactions? Give an example where violating each would cause problems.",
  "response_text": "The ACID properties of database transactions are Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, and Durability.\n\n1. Atomicity: Each transaction is treated as a single, indivisible unit of work. If any part of the transaction fails, the entire transaction fails, and the database is left unchanged. Violating atomicity can lead to inconsistent data. For example, consider a bank transfer where two accounts are debited and credited. If the system crashes after debiting one account but before crediting the other, the money is lost.\n\n2. Consistency: Transactions bring the database from one valid state to another. This property ensures that all rules and constraints are followed. Violating consistency can lead to invalid data. For example, if a transaction tries to insert a record with a duplicate primary key, it should be rejected to maintain consistency.\n\n3. Isolation: Transactions are executed in isolation, meaning the changes made by one transaction are not visible to other transactions until the first transaction is committed. Violating isolation can lead to inconsistent views of the data. For example, in a banking system, if two transactions are executed concurrently and one checks the balance before the other updates it, the second transaction might see an incorrect balance.\n\n4. Durability: Once a transaction is committed, its changes are permanent and protected from loss, even in the event of a system failure. Violating durability can lead to lost data. For example, if a transaction is committed but the data is not actually written to the disk before the system crashes, the data may be lost.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 10\nV (Verbal Fluency): 10\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 10\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 10\nQ (Query Interpretation): 10\nC (Contextual Awareness): 10\nY (Affective Modeling): 5\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 10\n---END RATINGS---",
